// name: daeModeHomotopy
// keywords: daeMode homotopy initialization flow reversal IDA
// status: correct
//
// daeMode (IDA) simulation of a degenerate start operating point. Both flowsheets
// start with the mover at zero speed and zero flow (m_flow_start = 0). The mover is
// a prescribed-flow machine, so its pressure characteristic is solved inversely for
// the normalised speed y_actual; that characteristic scales with y_actual^2, so its
// derivative vanishes at zero speed. Homotopy regularises this during *initialization*
// (as the specification requires) and is over once initialization finishes.
//
// Previously daeMode promoted that implicit loop to a global IDA algebraic variable,
// which placed the singular characteristic directly in the global Jacobian that IDA
// factorizes at t = 0, so the run failed with IDA_LSETUP_FAIL (-6). daeMode now keeps
// such implicit single-variable loops as local (torn) nonlinear systems, exactly as
// ODE mode does, so y_actual is solved inside the residual evaluation and never enters
// IDA's global Jacobian. The models therefore initialize and simulate without any
// non-zero m_flow_start workaround. Example2 additionally exercises a bidirectional
// (allowFlowReversal = true) resistor. See #15882.

setCommandLineOptions("--daeMode"); getErrorString();
loadFile("Example1Total.mo"); getErrorString();
simulate(Example1_total, stopTime=1.0, numberOfIntervals=20); getErrorString();
abs(val(res.m_flow, 1.0) - 1.0/30.0) < 1e-3;

loadFile("Example2Total.mo"); getErrorString();
simulate(Example2_total, stopTime=1.0, numberOfIntervals=20); getErrorString();
abs(val(res.m_flow, 1.0) - 1.0/30.0) < 1e-3;

// Result:
// true
// ""
// true
// ""
